00044 /*
00045  * Open the files.
00046  */
00047 bool CHPCompareGCOStoGCOS::OpenFiles(const char *file1, const char *file2)
00048 {
00049         gcos1.SetFileName(file1);
00050         if (gcos1.Read() == false)
00051         {
00052                 differences = "Failed to read the GCOS file\r\n";
00053                 return false;
00054         }
00055         gcos2.SetFileName(file2);
00056         if (gcos2.Read() == false)
00057         {
00058                 differences = "Failed to read the GCOS file\r\n";
00059                 return false;
00060         }
00061         return true;
00062 }

00064 /*
00065  * Compare the versions.
00066  */
00067 bool CHPCompareGCOStoGCOS::CompareFiles(const char *file1, const char *file2)
00068 {
00069         Clear();
00070         if (OpenFiles(file1, file2) == false)
00071                 return false;
00072         CompareFiles();
00073         return (differences.length() == 0);
00074 }

00101         CCHPFileHeader &ghead1 = gcos1.GetHeader();

00103 
00104         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(ghead1.GetCols(), ghead2.GetCols(), differences, "columns");
00105         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(ghead1.GetRows(), ghead2.GetRows(), differences, "rows");
00106         if (ghead1.GetAssayType() != CCHPFileHeader::Resequencing)
00107                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(ghead1.GetNumProbeSets(), ghead2.GetNumProbeSets(), differences, "entry count");
00108         CHPCompareUtils::CompareStrings(ghead1.GetChipType(), ghead2.GetChipType(), differences, "array type");
00109         CHPCompareUtils::CompareStrings(ghead1.GetAlgName(), ghead2.GetAlgName(), differences, "alg name");
00110         CHPCompareUtils::CompareStrings(ghead1.GetAlgVersion(), ghead2.GetAlgVersion(), differences, "alg version");
00111         CHPCompareUtils::CompareStrings(ghead1.GetParentCellFile(), ghead2.GetParentCellFile(), differences, "parent cel");

00121         TagValuePairTypeList &gparams2 = gcos2.GetHeader().AlgorithmParameters();

00131         {

00197 /*
00198  * Compare the data
00199  */
00200 void CHPCompareGCOStoGCOS::CompareData()
00201 {
00202         if (gcos1.GetHeader().GetAssayType() == CCHPFileHeader::Expression)
00203                 CompareExpression();
00204 
00205         else if (gcos1.GetHeader().GetAssayType() == CCHPFileHeader::Genotyping)
00206                 CompareGenotyping();
00207 
00208         else if (gcos1.GetHeader().GetAssayType() == CCHPFileHeader::Universal)
00209                 CompareUniversal();
00210 
00211         else if (gcos1.GetHeader().GetAssayType() == CCHPFileHeader::Resequencing)
00212                 CompareResequencing();
00213 }

00216  * Compare the expression results
00217  */
00218 void CHPCompareGCOStoGCOS::CompareExpression()
00219 {
00220         int n=gcos1.GetHeader().GetNumProbeSets();
00221         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00222         {
00223                 CExpressionProbeSetResults *gentry1 = gcos1.GetExpressionResults(i);
00224                 CExpressionProbeSetResults *gentry2 = gcos2.GetExpressionResults(i);
00225 
00226                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->DetectionPValue, gentry2->DetectionPValue, differences, "detection p-value");
00227                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->Signal, gentry2->Signal, differences, "signal"); 
00228                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->NumPairs, gentry2->NumPairs, differences, "pairs");
00229                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->NumUsedPairs, gentry2->NumUsedPairs, differences, "pairs used");
00230                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->Detection, gentry2->Detection, differences, "detection");
00231                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->m_HasCompResults, gentry2->m_HasCompResults, differences, "comp flag");
00232                 if (gentry1->m_HasCompResults)
00233                 {
00234                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->ChangePValue, gentry2->ChangePValue, differences, "change p-value"); 
00235                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->SignalLogRatio, gentry2->SignalLogRatio, differences, "slr"); 
00236                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->SignalLogRatioLow, gentry2->SignalLogRatioLow, differences, "slr-low"); 
00237                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gentry1->SignalLogRatioHigh, gentry2->SignalLogRatioHigh, differences, "slr-high"); 
00238                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->NumCommonPairs, gentry2->NumCommonPairs, differences, "common pairs");
00239                         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gentry1->Change, gentry2->Change, differences, "change");
00240                 }
00241         }
00242 }

00281  * Compare resequencing results.
00282  */
00283 void CHPCompareGCOStoGCOS::CompareResequencing()
00284 {
00285         CResequencingResults *gresults1 = gcos1.GetResequencingResults();
00286         CResequencingResults *gresults2 = gcos2.GetResequencingResults();
00287         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gresults1->GetCalledBasesSize(), gresults2->GetCalledBasesSize(), differences, "base count");
00288         if (gresults1->GetCalledBasesSize() != gresults2->GetCalledBasesSize())
00289                 return;
00290 
00291         int n=gresults1->GetCalledBasesSize();
00292         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00293         {
00294                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gresults1->GetCalledBase(i), gresults2->GetCalledBase(i), differences, "base call");
00295                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareFloats(gresults1->GetScore(i), gresults2->GetScore(i), differences, "base score");
00296         }
00297 
00298         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gresults1->GetForceCallsSize(), gresults2->GetForceCallsSize(), differences, "force size");
00299         if (gresults1->GetForceCallsSize() != gresults2->GetForceCallsSize())
00300                 return;
00301         n=gresults1->GetForceCallsSize();
00302         ForceCallType gf1;
00303         ForceCallType gf2;
00304         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00305         {
00306                 gf1 = gresults1->GetForceCall(i);
00307                 gf2 = gresults2->GetForceCall(i);
00308                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gf1.position, gf2.position, differences, "force position");
00309                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gf1.call, gf2.call, differences, "force call");
00310                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gf1.reason, gf2.reason, differences, "force reason");
00311         }
00312 
00313         CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(gresults1->GetOrigCallsSize(), gresults2->GetOrigCallsSize(), differences, "orig size");
00314         if (gresults1->GetOrigCallsSize() != gresults2->GetOrigCallsSize())
00315                 return;
00316         n=gresults1->GetOrigCallsSize();
00317         BaseCallType go1;
00318         BaseCallType go2;
00319         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00320         {
00321                 go1 = gresults1->GetOrigCall(i);
00322                 go2 = gresults2->GetOrigCall(i);
00323                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(go1.position, go2.position, differences, "orig position");
00324                 CHPCompareUtils::CompareInts(go1.call, go2.call, differences, "orig call");
00325         }
